## Performance

Tested with SMS_P512.ne30pg2_r05_IcoswISC30E3r5.WCYCL1850NS (512 MPI tasks):
  Total run: 495s for 5 simulated days (~99s/day)
  ATM: 288s (58%), OCN: 137s (28%), ICE: 36s (7%), LND: 23s (5%)

FME overhead is folded into component timing (no separate timer).
Remapped output is small relative to native: e.g., derived fields
remapped file is 775K vs 107M native (720x smaller). The SpMV
remap + PIO write is cheap compared to the model physics.

To quantify overhead precisely, run the same case without the
fme_output testmod and compare OCN/ICE component times.

Native-grid FME output is large for depth coarsening (1.1G/day at
1-degree resolution). When using remapped output only, set
output_stream='none' to suppress native output and save disk space.

